race.comment: EGERTON (6) resumes. She's a very lightly raced 6yo mare with a good record, winning two in a row at Pakenham over 1000m last time in before striking a heavy track at Mornington. She's got a sharp turn of foot and with the right run she can prove too good late. INNOCENT ENUFF (5) struggled last time at Bendigo but had been racing consistently prior and fancy coming back to 1000m will be no issue at all. She'll be up on speed and giving a sight. CAVALLO RAMPANTE (1) hasn't won in a while but was close up last time and can run well on an each way basis. GROUSE MOUNTAIN (2) has run some good races at 1000m without winning, he should run another honest race.
